forward Antonio Davis, whose play as an Indiana Pacer led the
Knicks to acquire Marcus Camby. Now Davis is a Raptor. By Mike
Wise.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Lead item: Chris Singleton is one-third
of an excellent young outfield that is an integral segment of the
team that had the best record in the American League entering the
weekend. The White Sox have played so well that they had led the
perennial AL Central champion Cleveland Indians for eight
consecutive days through Friday. The last time the Indians were out
of first place for that long was in April 1996. By Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Lead item on Cris Carter, the Minnesota
Vikings' receiver who may be entering his last season. By Mike
Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-NOTEBOOK (Toronto) _ Lead item: Antonio Davis didn't want to
leave the Indiana Pacers, and Charles Oakley turned down the
Lakers. Now they are the frontcourt bodyguards for Vince Carter in
Toronto. By Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   BOX-HEAVYWEIGHTS (Undated) _ The heavyweight division has
customarily been boxing's royalty for obvious reasons, and it has
traditionally provided the marquee fights and the sport's most
dominant personalities. But it is a division in flux, with an
uncertain future. By Bill Pennington.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-DERBY (Undated) _ Horse Racing notebook: Countdown to the
Kentucky Derby, May 6. By Joseph Durso.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTSBIZ (Undated) _ The newest game in sports: buying and
selling teams. By Richard Sandomir.
</P>
