<P>
   BC-YUGO-DIPLOMACY-NYT (moved Saturday, April 15)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, April 15
about the faltering United States effort to isolate the government
of Yugoslavia, referred incorrectly to the status of the Canadian
Embassy in Belgrade during NATO's air campaign against Yugoslavia
last year. It did not remain open during the bombing. The embassy
suspended operations on March 23, the day before the campaign
began, and reopened in October.
</P>
